    {
      "content": "View and manage StorSimple alerts | Microsoft Azure",
      "pos": [
        27,
        78
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Describes StorSimple alert conditions and severity, how to configure alert notifications, and how to use the StorSimple Manager service to manage alerts.",
      "pos": [
        96,
        249
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Use the StorSimple Manager service to view and manage StorSimple alerts",
      "pos": [
        531,
        602
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Overview",
      "pos": [
        607,
        615
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Alerts<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab in the StorSimple Manager service provides a way for you to review and clear StorSimple device–related alerts on a real-time basis.",
      "pos": [
        617,
        767
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "From this tab, you can centrally monitor the health of your StorSimple devices and the overall Microsoft Azure StorSimple solution.",
      "pos": [
        768,
        899
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This tutorial describes common alert conditions, alert severity levels, and how to configure alert notifications.",
      "pos": [
        901,
        1014
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Additionally, it includes alert quick reference tables, which enable you to quickly locate a specific alert and respond appropriately.",
      "pos": [
        1015,
        1149
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alerts page",
      "pos": [
        1153,
        1164
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Common alert conditions",
      "pos": [
        1223,
        1246
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Your StorSimple device generates alerts in response to a variety of conditions.",
      "pos": [
        1248,
        1327
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following are the most common types of alert conditions:",
      "pos": [
        1328,
        1388
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Hardware issues<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – These alerts tell you about the health of your hardware.",
      "pos": [
        1392,
        1470
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "They let you know if firmware upgrades are needed, if a network interface has issues, or if there is a problem with one of your data drives.",
      "pos": [
        1471,
        1611
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Connectivity issues<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – These alerts occur when there is difficulty in transferring data between data sources.",
      "pos": [
        1615,
        1727
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Communication issues can occur during transfer of data to and from the Azure storage account or due to lack of connectivity between the devices and the StorSimple Manager service.",
      "pos": [
        1728,
        1907
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "They can occur during configuration, backup, or restore processes.",
      "pos": [
        1908,
        1974
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Communication issues are some of the hardest to fix because there are so many points of failure.",
      "pos": [
        1975,
        2071
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should always first verify that network connectivity and Internet access are available before continuing on to more advanced troubleshooting.",
      "pos": [
        2072,
        2217
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2221,
        2353
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Performance issues<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – These alerts are caused when your system isn’t performing optimally, such as when it is under a heavy load."
    },
    {
      "content": "In addition, you might see alerts related to security, updates, or job failures.",
      "pos": [
        2355,
        2435
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alert severity levels",
      "pos": [
        2440,
        2461
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alerts have different severity levels, depending on the impact that the alert situation will have and the need for a response to the alert.",
      "pos": [
        2463,
        2602
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The severity levels are:",
      "pos": [
        2603,
        2627
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Critical<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – This alert is in response to a condition that is affecting the successful performance of your system.",
      "pos": [
        2631,
        2747
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Action is required to ensure that the StorSimple service is not interrupted.",
      "pos": [
        2748,
        2824
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Warning<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – This condition could become critical if not resolved.",
      "pos": [
        2828,
        2895
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should investigate the situation and take any action required to clear the issue.",
      "pos": [
        2896,
        2981
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2985,
        3091
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Information<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – This alert contains information that can be useful in tracking and managing your system."
    },
    {
      "content": "Configure alert settings",
      "pos": [
        3096,
        3120
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can choose whether you want to be notified by email of alert conditions for each of your StorSimple devices.",
      "pos": [
        3122,
        3234
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Additionally, you can identify other alert notification recipients by entering their email addresses in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OTHER EMAIL RECIPIENTS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> box, separated by semicolons.",
      "pos": [
        3235,
        3399
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3402,
        3472
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> You can enter a maximum of 20 email addresses per device."
    },
    {
      "content": "After you enable email notification for a device, members of the notification list will receive an email message each time a critical alert occurs.",
      "pos": [
        3474,
        3621
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The messages will be sent from <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>storsimple-alerts-noreply@mail.windowsazure.com<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> and will describe the alert condition.",
      "pos": [
        3622,
        3741
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Recipients can click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Unsubscribe<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to remove themselves from the email notification list.",
      "pos": [
        3742,
        3833
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To enable email notification of alerts for a device",
      "pos": [
        3840,
        3891
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3896,
        3945
      ],
      "content": "Go to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Devices<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> &gt; <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Configure<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> for the device."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3950,
        3994
      ],
      "content": "Under <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Alert Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, set the following:"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4003,
        4060
      ],
      "content": "In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SEND EMAIL NOTIFICATION<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field, select <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>YES<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4069,
        4235
      ],
      "content": "In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>EMAIL SERVICE ADMINISTRATORS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field, select <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>YES<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> if you wish to have the service administrator and all co-administrators receive the alert notifications."
    },
    {
      "content": "In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OTHER EMAIL RECIPIENTS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field, enter the email addresses of all other recipients who should receive the alert notifications.",
      "pos": [
        4244,
        4378
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enter names in the format <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>someone@somewhere.com<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4379,
        4429
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Use semicolons to separate the email addresses.",
      "pos": [
        4430,
        4477
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can configure a maximum of 20 email addresses per device.",
      "pos": [
        4478,
        4539
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alerts notification configuration page",
      "pos": [
        4548,
        4586
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To send a test email notification, click the arrow icon next to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SEND TEST EMAIL<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4658,
        4742
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The StorSimple Manager service will display status messages as it forwards the test notification.",
      "pos": [
        4743,
        4840
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4846,
        4895
      ],
      "content": "When the following message appears, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OK<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Alerts test notification email sent",
      "pos": [
        4904,
        4939
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> If the test notification message can't be sent, the StorSimple Manager service will display an appropriate message.",
      "pos": [
        5014,
        5142
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This can occur because of traffic or other network issues.",
      "pos": [
        5143,
        5201
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OK<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, wait a few minutes, and then try to send your test notification message again.",
      "pos": [
        5202,
        5294
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "View and track alerts",
      "pos": [
        5300,
        5321
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The StorSimple Manager service dashboard provides you with a quick glance at the number of alerts on your devices, broken down by severity level.",
      "pos": [
        5323,
        5468
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alerts dashboard",
      "pos": [
        5472,
        5488
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Clicking the severity level opens the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Alerts<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab.",
      "pos": [
        5552,
        5605
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The results include only the alerts that match that severity level.",
      "pos": [
        5606,
        5673
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alerts report scoped to alert type",
      "pos": [
        5677,
        5711
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Clicking an alert in the list provides you with additional details for the alert, including the last time the alert was reported, the number of occurrences of the alert on the device, and the recommended action to resolve the alert.",
      "pos": [
        5772,
        6004
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If it is a hardware alert, it will also identify the hardware component.",
      "pos": [
        6005,
        6077
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Hardware alert example",
      "pos": [
        6081,
        6103
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can copy the alert details to a text file if you want to track the alert resolution in a separate file or if you need to send the information to Microsoft Support.",
      "pos": [
        6166,
        6333
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After you have resolved the alert condition, you should clear the alert from the device by selecting the alert in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Alerts<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab and clicking <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Clear<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        6334,
        6490
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To clear multiple alerts, press the Ctrl key while you select the alerts, and then click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Clear<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        6491,
        6590
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that some alerts are automatically cleared when the issue is resolved or when the system updates the alert with new information.",
      "pos": [
        6591,
        6724
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Clear<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, you will have the opportunity to provide comments about the alert and the steps that you took to resolve the issue.",
      "pos": [
        6726,
        6867
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Some events will be cleared by the system if another event is triggered with new information.",
      "pos": [
        6868,
        6961
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In that case, you will see the following message.",
      "pos": [
        6962,
        7011
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Clear alert message",
      "pos": [
        7015,
        7034
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Sort and review alerts",
      "pos": [
        7104,
        7126
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You may find it more efficient to run reports on alerts so that you can review and clear them in groups.",
      "pos": [
        7128,
        7232
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Additionally, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Alerts<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab can display up to 250 alerts.",
      "pos": [
        7233,
        7295
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you have exceeded that number of alerts, not all alerts will be displayed in the default view.",
      "pos": [
        7296,
        7393
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can combine the following fields to customize which alerts are displayed:",
      "pos": [
        7394,
        7471
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Status<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – You can display either <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Active<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> or <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Cleared<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> alerts.",
      "pos": [
        7475,
        7544
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Active alerts are still being triggered on your system, while cleared alerts have been either manually cleared by an administrator or programmatically cleared because the system updated the alert condition with new information.",
      "pos": [
        7545,
        7772
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7776,
        7928
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Severity<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – You can display alerts of all severity levels (critical, warning, information), or just a certain severity, such as only critical alerts."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7932,
        8078
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Source<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – You can display alerts from all sources, or limit the alerts to those that come from either the service or one or all of the devices."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8082,
        8233
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Time range<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – By specifying the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>From<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>To<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> dates and time stamps, you can look at alerts during the time period that you are interested in."
    },
